{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-tag-tsx","path":"/tags/management/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"jmsbrdy"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"totalCount":3,"edges":[{"node":{"excerpt":"Being fixated on planning at the moment, the truism of how important it is to carefully pick the metrics by which you define success lingers in the back of my mind. You get what you measure It strikes me that the only measurable metric which we can be assured will be discussed, extrapolated, and…","fields":{"slug":"/picking-metrics/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"June 22, 2020","title":"A referendum on metrics we care about as a society","thumbnail":null,"staticThumbnail":null}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"Does anyone actually do product roadmaps any more? If so: how? And why? At university, we discussed the launch of a space shuttle as a classic example of where iterative software development wouldn’t work, and waterfall reigned supreme: there’s no such thing as an MVP and you don’t really get to do a bug fix update if your V1 didn’t work. But today, even NASA is doing Agile. What should a medium- and long-term plan look like in this context?","fields":{"slug":"/are-roadmaps-useful/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"June 21, 2020","title":"Are roadmaps useful any more?","thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.0491803278688525,"src":"/static/a13f52f814883027ea245fdf6bc2dbc6/07af2/hard-turn.jpg","srcSet":"/static/a13f52f814883027ea245fdf6bc2dbc6/684c4/hard-turn.jpg 64w,\n/static/a13f52f814883027ea245fdf6bc2dbc6/6d25d/hard-turn.jpg 128w,\n/static/a13f52f814883027ea245fdf6bc2dbc6/07af2/hard-turn.jpg 256w,\n/static/a13f52f814883027ea245fdf6bc2dbc6/57dc6/hard-turn.jpg 384w,\n/static/a13f52f814883027ea245fdf6bc2dbc6/49b36/hard-turn.jpg 512w,\n/static/a13f52f814883027ea245fdf6bc2dbc6/a6173/hard-turn.jpg 524w","sizes":"(max-width: 256px) 100vw, 256px"}}},"staticThumbnail":null}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"As described in an earlier post, I’ve been using James Clear’s Atomic Habits as a tool over the last few months. The focus on process and incremental gains has been useful, and leaves one with a fairly clear set of steps to work through – unlike many self-improvement books. It got me to thinking, though, how could the same approach be applied to a team or company?","fields":{"slug":"/atomic-habits-for-organisations/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"June 18, 2020","title":"Atomic Habits for organisations","thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.4883720930232558,"src":"/static/1c57faf773b37f1216137ab947f70f95/61fd6/the-habit-loop.png","srcSet":"/static/1c57faf773b37f1216137ab947f70f95/49ddd/the-habit-loop.png 64w,\n/static/1c57faf773b37f1216137ab947f70f95/62915/the-habit-loop.png 128w,\n/static/1c57faf773b37f1216137ab947f70f95/61fd6/the-habit-loop.png 256w,\n/static/1c57faf773b37f1216137ab947f70f95/450e9/the-habit-loop.png 384w,\n/static/1c57faf773b37f1216137ab947f70f95/bc59e/the-habit-loop.png 512w,\n/static/1c57faf773b37f1216137ab947f70f95/12b05/the-habit-loop.png 836w","sizes":"(max-width: 256px) 100vw, 256px"}}},"staticThumbnail":null}}}]}},"pageContext":{"tag":"management"}}}